{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "eazyvtc-chat-sprint5",
    "name": "EazyVTC API — Chat",
    "description": "# EazyVTC — Module Chat (Sprint 5)\n\n## Endpoints couverts\n- `POST /chat/reservations/:reservationId/messages` → Envoyer un message\n- `GET  /chat/reservations/:reservationId/messages` → Historique paginé\n- `GET  /admin/chat`                                → Vue admin des conversations actives\n\n## Architecture\nLes messages sont stockés dans `chat_messages`. Supabase Realtime diffuse chaque INSERT aux clients abonnés au canal `chat:reservation:{id}`. Le backend ne maintient pas de WebSocket — il expose uniquement des routes REST.\n\n## Prérequis\n1. Lancer l'API : `npm run dev`\n2. Avoir dans Supabase :\n   - Un compte `client@test.com` (rôle client)\n   - Un compte `driver@test.com` (rôle driver, statut active, assigné à une réservation)\n   - Un compte `admin@test.com` (rôle admin)\n3. Avoir une réservation en statut `assigned` ou `in_progress` appartenant au client de test\n\n## Ordre d'exécution recommandé\n1. **🔐 Setup — Tokens** : obtenir les 3 tokens\n2. **🔍 Setup — Réservation** : trouver et sauvegarder une reservation_id valide\n3. **💬 Client — Envoyer un message** : POST (sauvegarde message_id)\n4. **📖 Client — Historique** : GET avec pagination\n5. **🚗 Driver — Envoyer un message** : POST depuis le compte chauffeur\n6. **👨‍💼 Admin — Vue conversations** : GET /admin/chat\n7. **🔒 Contrôle d'accès** : vérifier 401 / 403 / 400 / 404\n\n## Variables sauvegardées automatiquement\n- `client_token`, `driver_token`, `admin_token`\n- `client_user_id` — pour les assertions admin\n- `reservation_id` — depuis la liste des réservations client\n- `message_id` — après envoi du premier message",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",       "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_token",   "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_token",   "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "admin_token",    "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_user_id", "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Sauvegardé depuis Login Client" },
    { "key": "reservation_id", "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "ID d'une réservation assigned/in_progress — sauvegardé via 'Get mes réservations'" },
    { "key": "message_id",     "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Sauvegardé après le premier POST message client" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔐 Setup — Tokens",
      "description": "Exécuter ces 3 requêtes en premier pour remplir client_token, driver_token et admin_token.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "Login Client",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"client@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Client1234!\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('client_token + client_user_id sauvegardés', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('client_token', data.access_token);",
                "  if (data.user?.id) {",
                "    pm.collectionVariables.set('client_user_id', data.user.id);",
                "    console.log('client_user_id:', data.user.id);",
                "  }",
                "  console.log('client_token OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "Login Driver",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"driver@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Driver1234!\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('driver_token sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_token', data.access_token);",
                "  console.log('driver_token OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "Login Admin",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin1234!\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('admin_token sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', data.access_token);",
                "  console.log('admin_token OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "🔍 Setup — Réservation test",
      "description": "Trouver une réservation assigned ou in_progress appartenant au client de test. Sauvegarde automatiquement reservation_id.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "Get mes réservations (client) — sauvegarde reservation_id",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations?status=assigned&limit=5",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["reservations"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "status", "value": "assigned" },
                { "key": "limit",  "value": "5" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('reservation_id sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  const reservations = data.reservations ?? data.data ?? data;",
                "  if (Array.isArray(reservations) && reservations.length > 0) {",
                "    pm.collectionVariables.set('reservation_id', reservations[0].id);",
                "    console.log('reservation_id:', reservations[0].id);",
                "  } else {",
                "    console.warn('Aucune réservation assigned trouvée — saisir reservation_id manuellement');",
                "  }",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "💬 Client — Envoyer un message",
      "description": "POST /chat/reservations/:reservationId/messages — Nécessite client_token et reservation_id.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "[Client] Envoyer un message — OK",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/messages",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["chat", "reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "messages"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"content\": \"Bonjour, je serai en bas dans 5 minutes.\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                "pm.test('Message retourné avec les bons champs', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('id');",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('reservation_id');",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('sender_id');",
                "  pm.expect(data.sender_role).to.equal('client');",
                "  pm.expect(data.content).to.equal('Bonjour, je serai en bas dans 5 minutes.');",
                "  pm.expect(data.read_at).to.be.null;",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('created_at');",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('message_id', data.id);",
                "  console.log('message_id:', data.id);",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[Client] Envoyer un deuxième message",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/messages",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["chat", "reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "messages"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"content\": \"Je suis au niveau de la porte principale.\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                "pm.test('Second message envoyé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data.content).to.equal('Je suis au niveau de la porte principale.');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "📖 Client — Historique des messages",
      "description": "GET /chat/reservations/:reservationId/messages — Historique paginé, marque les messages comme lus.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "[Client] Historique — page 1 (défaut)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/messages",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["chat", "reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "messages"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('Structure paginée correcte', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('messages').that.is.an('array');",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('total').that.is.a('number');",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('page').that.equal(1);",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('limit').that.equal(50);",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('total_pages');",
                "});",
                "pm.test('Messages triés par created_at ASC', () => {",
                "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  if (data.messages.length >= 2) {",
                "    const t1 = new Date(data.messages[0].created_at).getTime();",
                "    const t2 = new Date(data.messages[1].created_at).getTime();",
                "    pm.expect(t1).to.be.at.most(t2);",
                "  }",
                "});",
                "pm.test('Chaque message a les champs attendus', () => {",
                "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  if (data.messages.length > 0) {",
                "    const msg = data.messages[0];",
                "    pm.expect(msg).to.have.all.keys('id', 'reservation_id', 'sender_id', 'sender_role', 'content', 'read_at', 'created_at');",
                "  }",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[Client] Historique — pagination (page=1&limit=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/messages?page=1&limit=1",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["chat", "reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "messages"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page",  "value": "1" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "1" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('Limite appliquée — max 1 message retourné', () => {",
                "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(data.messages.length).to.be.at.most(1);",
                "  pm.expect(data.limit).to.equal(1);",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
